body.en-CA:
## Chief Executive Officer, Sunwing Vacations Group

A seasoned executive in the Canadian travel and tourism industry, Stephen Hunter brings three decades of travel expertise to Sunwing Vacations Group, combining experience from the shop floor up with astute business acumen and strategic vision. 

As the companys Chief Executive Officer, Stephen has oversight for Sunwing Vacations Groups day-to-day operations across the groups vacation and retail travel brands, along with overseeing product development, sales and business development. 

In 2002, Sunwing Vacations was launched as a new offering of all inclusive vacation packages to the sunny south from Eastern Canada. The company has grown steadily since its inception, now offering vacation packages to over 700 hotels  the largest assortment of any vacation provider in Canada  and direct flights from more than 25 airports across the country to over 30 sun destinations during the peak winter months.  

The success of Sunwing Vacations Group can largely be attributed to the innovative vision and entrepreneurial spirit that the company with Stephen Hunter at the helm has maintained from its inception until today. Always innovative and with an eye to future growth opportunities, Stephens leadership has placed Sunwing Vacations Group on the leading edge in the North American travel industry.

Cookies

When you visit our Website, we or one of our third party service providers may place a text file called a cookie in the browser directory of your computers hard drive. A cookie is a small piece of information that a website can store on your web browser and later retrieve information. The cookie cannot be read by any website other than the one that placed the cookie. Some browsers can be set to reject all cookies. If you choose to modify your browser in this manner, some pages of this Website may not function properly.

Upon your activation, these third party service providers may use cookies on our behalf to collect and store Internet log information, such as what time the visits occurred, whether the visitor has been to this site before, and what site referred the visitor to the web page. Geographic data may also determined by the IP Address of the visitors computer. If you activate such function, this information collected by the cookie may be transmitted to our third party service providers and may then be used to evaluate visitors behaviour and to generate statistical reports for the website activity on Sunwing Vacations Groups Website and may be used for marketing purposes.

You can choose to disable cookies in your browser at any time by following the procedure described in the Tools or Preferences menu in your browser. If you choose to modify your browser in this manner, some pages of the Website may not function properly.

content.en-CA:
__Discover Caribbean Bliss: Unveiling the Paradise of Tropical Escapes__

The Caribbean, a cluster of idyllic islands nestled in the heart of the azure Caribbean Sea, beckons travelers with its enchanting allure. Picture-perfect beaches, crystal-clear waters, and a vibrant blend of cultures make this region a haven for vacationers seeking a slice of paradise. Join us on a journey to explore the captivating world of Caribbean vacations.

The Caribbean's Endless Appeal
The Caribbean's magnetic appeal extends beyond its pristine beaches. It's a realm of natural wonders, rich history, and vibrant cultures that offer an array of experiences for every traveler. Here's why the Caribbean stands out:

Beaches Galore: The Caribbean boasts some of the world's most beautiful beaches, each with its unique charm. From the powdery white sands of Grace Bay in Turks and Caicos to the secluded coves of Antigua, these beaches are a sanctuary for sun-seekers.

Diverse Islands: The Caribbean is a mosaic of diverse islands, each with its character. Explore the lush rainforests of Saint Lucia, the vibrant culture of Jamaica, or the underwater wonders of the Bahamas. There's an island to suit every taste.

Water Adventures: The Caribbean's warm, clear waters make it a playground for water enthusiasts. Snorkeling, scuba diving, sailing, and deep-sea fishing are just a few of the aquatic adventures awaiting you.

Cultural Richness: Immerse yourself in the vibrant cultures of the Caribbean. Dance to the rhythms of reggae in Jamaica, savor the flavors of Creole cuisine in Martinique, or explore the colonial history of Puerto Rico's Old San Juan.

Caribbean Destinations: Where to Begin?
With so many enchanting islands to choose from, it's essential to pick the perfect destination for your Caribbean adventure:

The Bahamas: Dive into the cerulean waters of the Bahamas, home to the famous swimming pigs and the mysterious Dean's Blue Hole, one of the world's deepest underwater sinkholes.

Aruba: Known for its year-round sunshine and stunning beaches, Aruba is a windsurfing paradise and offers a vibrant nightlife scene.

Saint Martin/Sint Maarten: This dual-nation island boasts beautiful beaches, duty-free shopping, and two distinct cultures to explore, both French and Dutch.

Barbados: A treasure trove of history and culture, Barbados is famous for its friendly locals, vibrant festivals, and rum distilleries.

Planning Your Caribbean Escape
A well-planned Caribbean vacation ensures you make the most of your time in this tropical paradise:

Island Hopping: Given the proximity of many Caribbean islands, consider island-hopping to experience a variety of cultures and landscapes.

Cuisine Exploration: Savor the unique flavors of Caribbean cuisine, from jerk chicken in Jamaica to conch fritters in the Bahamas.

Local Experiences: Engage with locals, attend festivals, and participate in activities like rum tastings, snorkeling with sea turtles, or hiking through lush rainforests.

Relaxation and Adventure: Balance relaxation on the beach with thrilling adventures like zip-lining, hiking volcanic peaks, or exploring underwater caves.

A Caribbean vacation is a journey to a world of endless beauty, warm hospitality, and unforgettable moments. Whether you seek relaxation, adventure, or cultural immersion, the Caribbean islands offer a treasure trove of experiences waiting to be discovered. Let the Caribbean's enchanting charm sweep you off your feet and into the embrace of paradise. Your dream tropical escape starts here in the Caribbean.

content.value: A seasoned executive in the Canadian travel and tourism industry, Stephen Hunter brings three decades of travel expertise to Sunwing Vacations Group, combining experience from the shop floor up with astute business acumen and strategic vision. As the companys Chairman of the Board, Stephen is poised to advise on the strategic alignment and future growth of the vacations division.

In 2002, Sunwing Vacations was launched as a new offering of all inclusive vacation packages to the sunny south from Eastern Canada. The company has grown steadily since its inception, now offering vacation packages to over 700 hotels  the largest assortment of any vacation provider in Canada  and direct flights from more than 25 airports across the country to over 30 sun destinations during the peak winter months.

The success of Sunwing Vacations Group can largely be attributed to the innovative vision and entrepreneurial spirit that Stephen has embedded within the company. Always innovative and with an eye to future growth opportunities, Stephens strategic, growth-focused mindset has placed Sunwing Vacations Group on the leading edge in the North American travel industry.

Cadre chevronn de lindustrie canadienne du voyage et du tourisme, Stephen Hunter apporte au Groupe de Vacances Sunwing trois dcennies dexpertise dans le domaine, combinant lexprience de terrain  un sens aigu des affaires et  une vision stratgique. En tant que prsident du conseil dadministration de lentreprise, Stephen sengage  prodiguer des conseils pour lharmonisation stratgique et la croissance future de la division de vacances.

En 2002, Vacances Sunwing a t cr en tant que nouvelle offre de forfaits vacances tout compris vers les tropiques  partir de lEst du Canada. Depuis ses dbuts, lentreprise a connu une croissance constante. Elle offre maintenant des forfaits vacances dans plus de 700htels, la plus grande slection de tous les fournisseurs de vacances au Canada, et des vols directs  partir de plus de 25aroports  travers le pays vers plus de 30destinations soleil pendant lhiver.

Le succs du Groupe de Vacances Sunwing est largement attribuable  la vision novatrice et  lesprit entrepreneurial que Stephen Hunter a su implanter au sein de lentreprise. Toujours innovateur et attentif aux possibilits de croissance future, Stephen a utilis sa vision stratgique et axe sur la croissance pour placer le Groupe de Vacances Sunwing  lavant-garde de lindustrie du voyage en Amrique du Nord.

Samantha Taylor joined Sunwing in March 2020 as Chief Marketing Officer and, in August 2023 was appointed Chief Marketing & Digital Officer of Sunwing Vacations Group, the vacation division of the WestJet Group. She also joined WestJets executive leadership team in October 2023.

As Chief Marketing & Digital Officer, Samanthas portfolio includes leading all Marketing, Communications, Digital, Customer Data & Analytics, and People & Culture activities across Sunwing Vacations Group, which is comprised of Sunwing Vacations, WestJet Vacations, Vacation Express, SellOffVacations and Luxe Destination Weddings.

Before joining Sunwing, Samantha held a variety of executive leadership roles including Chief Marketing Officer at Indigo and Director of Sales and Consumer Products at Mattel. Consistently leveraging customer insights to drive innovation, Samanthas track record for growth and eye for brand marketing is a driving force behind Sunwing Vacations Group. Driven by data, research and digital marketing trends, Samantha uses an empathetic and people-first approach to bolster her team to excellence.
Samantha holds a Bachelors Degree from the University of Toronto in International Relations.

Andrew Dawson joined Sunwing in January 2009 as Chief Operating Officer and President of Tour Operations, and in August 2023 was appointed President of Sunwing Vacations Group, the vacation division of the WestJet Group. Andrew also joined WestJets executive leadership team in October 2023.

As President of Sunwing Vacations Group, Andrew oversees all aspects of the groups vacation and retail services, for brands including Sunwing Vacations, WestJet Vacations, Vacation Express, SellOffVacations and Luxe Destination Weddings.

Under Andrews direction over the past 14 years, Sunwings brands have grown to serve more than two and a half million travellers annually. As North Americas leading vacation travel provider, servicing Canadians from coast to coast and a growing US customer base through the US tour operator Vacation Express, Andrew continues to propel the WestJet Groups robust vacation offerings forward, providing North American customers with affordable leisure travel options to dozens of popular vacation destinations.

Prior to his executive-level positions with Sunwing, Andrew served as Interim President of TUI Travels Canadian businesses. He has also held previous leadership roles in Canada, the US and the UK with Airtours plc and Asda Stores.
Andrew qualified as a Chartered Management Accountant in the UK in 1991.
